HEADWORD: Gothicism
<hw>Goth"i*cism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
Gothic idiom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conformity to the Gothic style of
architecture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Rudeness of manners; barbarousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gothicize</ent>⟦br⟧
